The "Inaugural" She-Believes Cup.... Indicating future iterations. If that's so, it's a Good Thing. It would be a Better Thing, though, if it were not held in the same season as the Algarve Cup, a competition that gives more teams the rare opportunity for competitive matches. Womens' teams in general need more such, and a competition that annually steals away four of the top teams for what is, essentially, a fundraiser, will do more harm than good for the sport as a whole. And in the long run, those top teams will lose out as well. If you don't have real competition, you don't get better.



